# Cline Rules for inventory-app

## File Editing

- Always output the complete file content from start to finish when editing any file
- Never use `...`, `# unchanged`, `# rest of code`, `# existing code`, or any placeholder to skip sections
- Never truncate output mid-file under any circumstances
- Complete every file edit fully before stopping

## Task Approach

- Edit one file at a time, show the result, then move to the next
- If a task involves more than 3 files, list the files and order of edits first and wait for confirmation
- After each file edit, explicitly state what was changed and what file is next

## Django-Specific

- This is a multi-tenant Django app — always preserve business/user scoping in any view edits
- Never remove existing URL patterns, only add new ones
- Always keep existing migrations intact — never edit migration files

## Django Templates

- Never allow an HTML formatter (Prettier, ESLint, or any other) to touch .html files
- Django template tags {% %} and {{ }} must always stay on a single line — never wrap them
- {% trans 'string' %} tags must never be split across lines under any circumstances
- Never use Bootstrap utility classes that hardcode light backgrounds on dark-themed templates:
    - Forbidden: bg-light, bg-primary, bg-success, bg-danger, bg-warning, bg-info, bg-white
    - Forbidden: text-muted (use explicit color styles instead, e.g. style="color: #b0b0b0")
    - Forbidden: card bg-dark border-secondary (use inline styles for dark theme cards)
- Never add class="text-muted" to any element — always use explicit style="color: #b0b0b0"
- When adding helper/hint text under form fields, use style="color: #b0b0b0; font-size: 0.8rem"
- Never change var(--muted) references without first checking if the variable is defined in base.html
- The theme uses: --onyx, --gold, --pearl, --raspberry, --raspberry-dark as core CSS variables